---
const title = "Consulting (JSC)";
const brand = "JaiSellers Companies";
const division = "JaiSellers Consulting";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{title} — {brand}</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Governance, funding, and operations systems for mission-driven organizations—built to hold under real pressure."
    />
   <link rel="stylesheet" href="/site.css" />
  </head>

  <body>
    <header class="topbar">
      <a class="logo" href="/">{brand}</a>
      <nav class="nav">
        <a href="/consulting">Consulting (JSC)</a>
        <a href="/design">Design</a>
        <a href="/jsi">JSI</a>
        <a href="/about">About</a>
        <a class="nav-cta" href="/contact">Contact</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <!-- Intro -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="container">
          <p class="kicker">Consulting</p>
          <h1>{division}</h1>
          <p style="margin-top:14px; max-width:70ch;">
            We help mission-driven leaders turn conviction into governance, funding, and operating systems that hold up
            under real pressure—so your work survives transitions, grant cycles, and growth.
          </p>

          <div class="cta-row" style="margin-top:20px;">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/contact">Book a consult</a>
            <a class="btn ghost" href="/systems">See how we work</a>
          </div>

          <div class="trust-row" style="margin-top:18px;">
            <span class="pill">501(c)(3) formation</span>
            <span class="pill">Bylaws + governance</span>
            <span class="pill">Budgets + grant readiness</span>
            <span class="pill">Reporting + operating rhythms</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Offer Stack -->
      <section class="section section-alt">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>Offer stack</h2>
          <p style="max-width:70ch;">
            Choose the lane you need right now. We can start with a fast build, then deepen into ongoing support.
          </p>

          <div class="grid3" style="margin-top:18px;">
            <!-- Offer 1 -->
            <article class="card">
              <h3>Formation Machine</h3>
              <p>
                For new or rebuilding nonprofits that need structure first—so funding and credibility can follow.
              </p>
              <ul class="bullets">
                <li>EIN + incorporation review</li>
                <li>Bylaws + core policies (COI, records, etc.)</li>
                <li>Board roles + meeting rhythm</li>
                <li>1023/1023-EZ readiness plan</li>
                <li>Compliance checklist + 12-month calendar</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="small">Best for: 0–24 months old or reinstatement/rebuilds.</p>
              <a class="btn ghost" href="/contact" style="margin-top:12px;">Ask about Formation →</a>
            </article>

            <!-- Offer 2 -->
            <article class="card">
              <h3>Grant Readiness + Revenue Stack</h3>
              <p>
                For orgs doing good work but bleeding time and money because revenue systems aren’t built.
              </p>
              <ul class="bullets">
                <li>Budget architecture (program + admin)</li>
                <li>Grant calendar + pipeline tracker</li>
                <li>Case for support (funder-ready)</li>
                <li>Outcomes + reporting framework</li>
                <li>Submission workflow + file system</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="small">Best for: orgs with programs running but funding unstable.</p>
              <a class="btn ghost" href="/contact" style="margin-top:12px;">Build the Revenue Stack →</a>
            </article>

            <!-- Offer 3 -->
            <article class="card">
              <h3>Board Ops + Operating Rhythm</h3>
              <p>
                For orgs that are growing—but governance, meetings, and accountability are messy or inconsistent.
              </p>
              <ul class="bullets">
                <li>Board packet template + agenda system</li>
                <li>Policies + approvals workflow</li>
                <li>OKRs/KPIs (lightweight, usable)</li>
                <li>Monthly reporting cadence</li>
                <li>Role clarity + task ownership</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="small">Best for: orgs scaling programs or managing multiple grants.</p>
              <a class="btn ghost" href="/contact" style="margin-top:12px;">Stabilize Ops →</a>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Process -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>How it works</h2>
          <div class="grid3" style="margin-top:18px;">
            <article class="card">
              <h3>1) Quick intake</h3>
              <p>We clarify goals, urgency, constraints, and what “done” means. No vague projects.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="card">
              <h3>2) Build the system</h3>
              <p>Templates, checklists, policies, trackers, and a simple rhythm your team can actually maintain.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="card">
              <h3>3) Hand-off + sustain</h3>
              <p>We document it, train it, and set a maintenance cadence so it doesn’t decay after month one.</p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ / Fit -->
      <section class="section section-alt">
        <div class="container split">
          <div>
            <h2>Fit check</h2>
            <p style="margin-top:10px; max-width:70ch;">
              This is for mission-driven teams who want structure—not vibes. If you’re ready to do the work and keep the
              rhythm, we’ll build something durable.
            </p>

            <div class="grid3" style="margin-top:18px;">
              <article class="card">
                <h3>Good fit</h3>
                <ul class="bullets">
                  <li>You’re serious about compliance and clarity</li>
                  <li>You want templates + repeatable systems</li>
                  <li>You need funding to stop being random</li>
                </ul>
              </article>
              <article class="card">
                <h3>Not a fit</h3>
                <ul class="bullets">
                  <li>You want shortcuts or “guaranteed grants”</li>
                  <li>You won’t involve decision-makers</li>
                  <li>You refuse basic documentation</li>
                </ul>
              </article>
              <article class="card">
                <h3>Typical outputs</h3>
                <ul class="bullets">
                  <li>Board packet + calendar</li>
                  <li>Budget + pipeline tracker</li>
                  <li>Policies + filing checklist</li>
                </ul>
              </article>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="callout">
            <h3>Start here</h3>
            <p style="margin-top:10px;">
              Book a consult and we’ll decide the fastest path to stability.
            </p>
            <a class="btn primary" href="/contact" style="margin-top:12px;">Book a consult</a>
            <p class="small">Email: <a href="mailto:joshuajaisellers@gmail.com">joshuajaisellers@gmail.com</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="footer">
      <div class="container footer-inner">
        <span>© {new Date().getFullYear()} {brand}</span>
        <span class="sep">•</span>
        <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
